Conservation Example


@ajplus Here’s why foraging as a Black person is an act of rebellion, ft. @alexisnikole.




https://www.tiktok.com/@ajplus/video/7198294467445542187 - Conservation must be done in community, or will inevitably result in furthering inequity and injustice - For example, foraging - A skill used by Black and Indigenous people for milennia on this land - Intentionally removed in the name of “conservation” and as an act of racism - Reclaiming that practice in cities is part of reparing the relationship, conservation because Indigenous peoples are the stewards of this land, and increases food security
